The interface ist total in the sense that the observer receives all symbols emanating from the object.
(However, the object needs not receive all symbols emanating
from the observer.)

n𝑛italic-nn elementary objects carry n𝑛italic-nn bits of (classical) information [28]. The information content
present in the physical system is exhausted by the n𝑛italic-nn bits given;
nothing more can be gained by any perceivable procedure.
